						<div class="postbody">The protocol on the wire is IÂ²C, which is <em>comparatively</em> tolerant of bad routing, including forks in the path. It <strong>is</strong> asking for trouble, though.<br /><br />I don't think a pre-existing {Wii nunchuk} to {JST} adapter exists, but there's no reason you couldn't build your own.</div>

